@everyone , my personal take on this matter is to keep it simple and avoid the temptation of categorising too much (the taxonomical approach). On the other hand, I guess there is a long path ahead of us and we will be continously evaluating the convenience / usefulness of splitting or merging certain topics/themes.
There is one point worth highlighting, though: the network will eventually -maybe sooner than we expect- produce tools that analise, synthesise and organise information within the server. This was noted by Dr Sanchez as one of the key objectives, as the testing ground that this community is. This suggests that we should think strategically about the contents: communications, events and discussions vs documents / resources, etc..
Hope this makes sense...

